definition: any of those hardwood trees of the genus Dalbergia that yield rosewood--valuable cabinet woods of a dark red or purplish color streaked and variegated with black

name: silver ash
definition: any of various timber trees of the genus Flindersia

name: soapberry
definition: a tree of the genus Sapindus whose fruit is rich in saponin

name: southern beech
definition: any of various beeches of the southern hemisphere having small usually evergreen leaves

name: tulipwood tree
definition: any of various trees yielding variously colored woods similar to true tulipwood

name: willow (tree)
definition: any of numerous deciduous trees and shrubs of the genus Salix

name: yellowwood
definition: any of various trees having yellowish wood or yielding a yellow extract

name: zebrawood
definition: any of various trees or shrubs having mottled or striped wood

name: pollen
definition: the fine spores that contain male gametes and that are borne by an anther in a flowering plant

name: cyme
definition: more or less flat-topped cluster of flowers in which the central or terminal flower opens first

name: flower cluster
definition: an inflorescence consisting of a cluster of flowers

name: olive (drupe)
definition: one-seeded fruit of the European olive tree usually pickled and used as a relish

name: cherry (drupe)
definition: a red fruit with a single hard stone

name: plum (drupe)
definition: any of numerous varieties of small to medium-sized round or oval fruit having a smooth skin and a single pit

name: berry (edible fruit)
definition: any of numerous small and pulpy edible fruits; used as desserts or in making jams and jellies and preserves

name: citrus (edible fruit)
definition: any of numerous fruits of the genus Citrus having thick rind and juicy pulp; grown in warm regions

name: custard apple (edible fruit)
definition: the fruit of any of several tropical American trees of the genus Annona having soft edible pulp

name: dried fruit
definition: fruit preserved by drying

name: grape (edible fruit)
definition: any of various juicy fruit of the genus Vitis with green or purple skins; grow in clusters

name: melon (edible fruit)
definition: any of numerous fruits of the gourd family having a hard rind and sweet juicy flesh

name: passion fruit
definition: egg-shaped tropical fruit of certain passionflower vines; used for sherbets and confectionery and drinks

name: legume (pod)
definition: the fruit or seed of any of various bean or pea plants consisting of a case that splits along both sides when ripe and having the seeds attach to one side of the case

name: apple (edible fruit)
definition: fruit with red or yellow or green skin and sweet to tart crisp whitish flesh

name: pear (edible fruit)
definition: sweet juicy gritty-textured fruit available in many varieties

name: bean (seed)
definition: any of various seeds or fruits that are beans or resemble beans

name: edible seed
definition: many are used as seasoning

name: grain (seed)
definition: dry seed-like fruit produced by the cereal grasses: e.g. wheat, barley, Indian corn

name: nut (seed)
definition: usually large hard-shelled seed

name: oilseed
definition: any of several seeds that yield oil
